# Trivy vulnerability ignore list
# Keep in sync with pip-audit exemptions in .github/workflows/ci.yml
#
# These are Python build-tool CVEs found in the python:3.12-slim base image.
# Attack vectors are limited to malicious archive extraction at install time
# (not at application runtime) or JWT header handling in packages not directly
# used by the application. The Dockerfile already upgrades these packages to
# fixed versions, but dependency resolution or base-image bundled copies may
# retain older dist-info that Trivy detects.
#
# Each entry references the fixed version so this list can be pruned once
# a base image ships with the fixed versions by default.

# pip < 26.0 — path traversal during tar/wheel extraction (CVE-2025-8869, CVE-2026-1703)
# Fixed by Dockerfile: pip install --upgrade "pip>=26.0"
CVE-2025-8869
CVE-2026-1703

# setuptools < 78.1.1 — RCE / path traversal in package_index (CVE-2024-6345, CVE-2025-47273)
# Fixed by Dockerfile: pip install --upgrade "setuptools>=78.1.1"
CVE-2024-6345
CVE-2025-47273

# wheel < 0.46.2 — path traversal / arbitrary file permission change (CVE-2026-24049)
# Fixed by Dockerfile: pip install --upgrade "wheel>=0.46.2"
CVE-2026-24049

# PyJWT < 2.12.0 — unknown crit header extensions not validated (CVE-2026-32597)
# Application uses python-jose, not PyJWT directly; PyJWT enters as transitive dep.
# Fixed by Dockerfile: pip install --upgrade "PyJWT>=2.12.0"
CVE-2026-32597

# CVE-2026-4539 — same exemption as pip-audit (--ignore-vuln CVE-2026-4539).
CVE-2026-4539

# pip — concatenated tar+ZIP archive handling (CVE-2026-3219)
# No upstream fix released yet (pip 26.0.1 is the latest as of 2026-04-26).
# Attack surface: malicious archive extraction at install time only, not runtime.
# Same exemption as pip-audit (--ignore-vuln CVE-2026-3219). Remove once pip
# ships a fixed version.
CVE-2026-3219
